### Feature 2: Complete Federated Schema Generation

**As a developer**, I want to inspect the entire executable federated schema my subgraph SDL expands into, so I can verify the federation plumbing that gets injected on my behalf.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input request carries an operation selector of `federated_schema_sdl`, an `sdl` string, and a boolean `federationV2` flag indicating whether the subgraph targets the second-generation specification (the flag controls whether the printed schema includes an explicit schema-definition block). The transformer builds the full executable schema and prints its complete SDL. Unlike the service-discovery view, this output includes the synthetic plumbing that federation injects: the federation directive definitions, a union enumerating every resolvable entity type, the two service-discovery root fields added to the query type (one returning the wrapper object that carries the SDL document, one accepting a list of representations and returning the entity union), the wrapper object type itself, and the scalar types used for representations and key-field selections. Types, fields and directive declarations are emitted in a normalized order. Built-in GraphQL directives are not redeclared in the output.

