### Feature 3: Resolvable Entity Discovery

**As a developer**, I want the transformer to tell me which of my types are resolvable federation entities, so I can confirm my key annotations took effect and wire up the right reference resolvers.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input request carries an operation selector of `entities` and an `sdl` string. The transformer reports the resolvable entity types of the schema — the members of the entity union exposed by the federated schema. The output is a line giving the total entity count, followed by one line per entity type name, with the names listed in sorted order. A type is a resolvable entity when it carries a key marking it as resolvable; a type whose only key is explicitly marked non-resolvable is excluded, and a subgraph with no entity types reports a count of zero and emits no name lines.

